      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Full length shot of a group of five men in urban clothes with military elements, all with fur caps and holding long rifles with bayonets. The group is arranged around artificial rocks in front of a painted canvas backdrop, which creates the illusion of the scene being set in nature.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">On the left side seated: <ref target="info:fedora/context:vase.pn.c3834c">Ivan Anastasov Karastoyanov</ref>. Among the photographed is Boris Kisimov (1867 - 1934), a politician, who in 1905 became Bulgarian trade agent and in 1910 Consul in Odessa.</ab>
